@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<style>
    .privacy-wrap {
        max-width: 640px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4.5rem 1rem 6rem;
    }

    .privacy-wrap .sprig {
        width: 46px;
        opacity: 0.8;
        margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
        display: block;
    }

    .privacy-wrap h1 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
        font-weight: 550;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        color: #3d3a35;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    .privacy-wrap p {
        font-family: 'Inter', 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.75;
        color: #6f6a62;
    }
</style>

<div class="privacy-wrap">
    <svg class="sprig" viewBox="0 0 60 40" fill="none" stroke="#c9688f" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M30 38 C30 24 30 14 30 6" />
        <path d="M30 20 C24 16 18 15 13 17 C17 23 24 24 30 22" />
        <path d="M30 14 C36 10 42 9 47 11 C43 17 36 18 30 16" />
        <circle cx="30" cy="5" r="3" />
    </svg>
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p>Your garden is your business. Flowerfinder only ever uses your photos to identify flowers, and nothing you snap is shared without your say-so.</p>
    <p>Flowerfinder doesn't ask you to create an account and doesn't collect, sell, or share personal information. There are no advertising trackers here.</p>
    <p>When the photo-identification feature arrives, pictures you upload will be used only to identify the flower in them — they won't be kept afterwards or used for anything else.</p>
    <p>Flower photography comes from Wikimedia Commons; each image remains the work of its original photographer.</p>
</div>
